==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foxed
<hw>Foxed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Discolored
or stained; -- said of timber, and also of the paper of books or
engravings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Repaired by foxing; <as>as, <ex>foxed</ex>
boots</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foxery</ent>⟦br⟧
